[Nouns] condemnation, conviction, judgment, penalty, sentence; proscription, damnation; death warrant.
attainder, attainture, attaintment.
[Verbs] condemn, convict, cast, bring home to, find guilty, damn, doom, sign the death warrant, sentence, pass sentence on, attaint, confiscate, proscribe, sequestrate; nonsuit.
disapprove [more]; accuse [more].
stand condemned.
[Adjectives] condemnatory, damnatory; condemned; nonsuited (failure) [more]; self-convicted.
